  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    Admin
    This dataclass is used to store Admins login credentials and to make the Admin recognized as such, as the LoginUser stored in the user's HttpSession (see LoginManager) can be typecasted back.
    Admin_  
    AdminDao
    Data Access Object providing methods to get Admin objects out of the Database
    AES256EncryptionUtil
    This util uses a 256 bit AES algorithm with Galois Counter Mode (GCM) provided by the SpringFramework.
    AES256EncryptionUtilTest  
    BaseServlet
    This abstract HttpServlet should be used for all created servlets, as it sets the character encoding and stops request, if request or response is null.
    Supported Methods: GET, POST, DELETE
    ChangePasswordServlet
    This HttpServlet can be used by Godfathers and Admins to change their own password.
    Allowed methods: POST
    Constants
    This class contains static attributes to use in fronted as well as in backend, so that a standard is guaranteed.
    Constants.Database
    This class contains all static attributes related to the database
    Constants.Godfather
    This class contains all static attributes related with a Godfather
    Constants.Login
    This class contains all static attributes related with the login.
    Constants.Security
    This class contains all static attributes that have influence about the security of this application.
    Constants.Trainee
    This class contains all static attributes related with Trainees
    CSRFForm
    Enum used to identify a frontend-form, that uses tokens, to protect against Cross-Site-Request-Forgery (CSRF).
    CSRFPreventionUtil
    This util should be used to prevent cross-site request forgery.
    CSRFPreventionUtilTest  
    CSRFServletFilter
    This filter can be used to make sure, that a request contains a valid csrf token.
    It can only be used by the FilterServlet and cannot be used by the native filter servlet mechanism, as it does not implement Filter.
    USAGE: SERVLET/REST only
    Dao<K,​E>
    Interface each data access object should implement, including methods to find an entry by id, list all entities, persist/update/remove an entity.
    DateTypeAdapter
    This TypeAdapter used with Gson for json convertions, converts a Date to a timestamp.
    DateUtil
    This util is used to simplify Date operations
    DateUtilTest  
    DefaultHttpSession  
    EmailPasswordLoginUser
    Abstract class that is used by all classes, that are using email and password as login credentials.
    EmailPasswordLoginUser_  
    EmailPasswordLoginUserDao<K,​E>
    Abstract Data Access Object, that can be used for all objects, that extend EmailPasswordLoginUser, to get their id, email and password
    EncryptionUtil
    This interface should be used for all encryption utils, so that they can be replaced easily.
    EntityManagerFactory
    This factory uses java's Persistence class to create an EntityManagerFactory and EntityManager's using the persistence settings file (src/main/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml).
    Pattern: Singleton
    FilterHandler
    This handler manages ServletFilters and checks, if a request applies to all filters.
    FilterServlet
    This abstract class extends the BaseServlet and expects ServletFilters (constructor), that check, if the request is valid (for example, if the user is logged in).
    Use BaseServlet instead, if a servlet should be publicly available without any restriction.
    FormatValidator
    Filters by a given Format
    GenerateTraineeTokenServlet
    This HttpServlet may be used by a Admin to generate new Tokens, that can be used by Trainees to login
    Allowed http methods: GET
    Godfather
    This dataclass is used for the godfather login and profile edit and for displaying all godfathers, when logged in as a trainee.
    Godfather_  
    GodfatherAddServlet
    This HttpServlet can be used by Admins to add a Godfather account.
    GodfatherDao
    Data Access Object providing methods to get Godfather objects out of the Database
    GodfatherFilterServlet
    This servlet is only available for Trainees and is used to filter available godfathers or - if the trainee already selected a godfahter - get information of their selected godfather.
    GodfatherImageServlet
    This HttpServlet is available for Trainees only and is used to get the image of a Godfather (set by Godfather).
    If no image is found (because the Godfather hasn't set one), error 404 is returned.
    GodfatherSelectServlet
    This servlet is used by trainees to select their godfather.
    GodfatherUpdateImageServlet
    HttpServlet to upload a profile picture
    Allowed methods: POST
    GodfatherUpdateServlet
    This Servlet is used by the Admin to update a Godfathers personal data (except password) or to remove the Godfather
    Allowed http methods: POST, DELETE
    GodfatherUpdateServlet
    Servlet that enables a godfather him/herselfs email-address, location, maxTrainees, description and picktext
    This Servlet is protected by a CSRFToken
    HashUtil
    This interface provides methods that are normally used with hash algorithms.
    HasName
    This interface can be used for simple database entities, that connect a id with a name
    HibernateUtil
    This util contains tools for the data access objects
    Id
    Abstract class containing an id-integer.
    Id_  
    IdDao<K,​E>
    Data Access Object, that can be used for all models, that extend from Id
    IdValidator
    Validates, that an database id is existent
    ImageManager
    The ImageManager is able to read and write godfather images from the default data source.
    Pattern: SINGLETON
    InputValidator
    The InputValidator interface can be used with the ParameterValidationFilter to protect a HttpServlet against invalid requests
    InputVerifyUtil
    This util can be used to verify inputs, especially when the data is given by the frontend.
    InputVerifyUtilTest  
    Job
    This dataclass contains informations regarding the different job types (for example "Auszubildender")
    Job_  
    JobDao
    Data Access Object providing methods to get Jobs out of the Database
    LengthValidator
    This InputValidator can check, if a string has at least a certain length
    Location
    This dataclass contains informations regarding a location
    Location_  
    LocationDao
    Data Access Object object providing methods to get Locations out of the Database
    LoggingManager
    This Manager can be used to get the default Logger of this project.
    LoginManager
    This class is used to read and write login data (see LoginUser) to the client's HttpSession.
    Pattern: Singleton
    LoginServlet
    This HttpServlet get's called by the client, when the user tries to log on.
    LoginServletFilter
    This filter checks, if a client is logged in.
    It can be used with the FilterServlet, as well as a native Filter.
    USAGE: SERVLET/REST, JSP/via WEB.XML
    LoginUser
    Baseclass of all classes, that can store data, which you can use to log on.
    LoginUser_  
    LogoutServlet
    This HttpServlet is used to remove the relation between the client's HttpSession and the logged in LoginUser.
    Allowed http methods: GET
    NumberUtil
    Util providing methods, that are useful when working with integers.
    NumberUtilTest  
    NumberValidator
    This InputValidator checks if a given String is a number and if it is in a range, if specified
    ParameterValidationFilter
    This filter can be used, if certain parameters are required.
    PatternValidator
    This InputValidator checks if a pattern can be applied
    PropertyUtil
    This util offers methods to read out of an ".properties" file stored in the /resource folder.
    Files have to conform Java's Properties format.
    RandomUtil
    This util may be used to generate random data
    RandomUtilTest  
    RedirectServlet
    This HttpServlet redirects the client to the default welcome page
    Allowed methods: GET
    ServletFilter
    Interface used for ServletFilters, that are used in the FilterServlet.
    It cannot be used by the native filter servlet mechanism (for jsp), as it does not extend Filter.
    ServletParameter
    This enum should unify the parameter names.
    ServletUtil
    This util offers methods, that can be used for HttpServlets.
    SHA256Util
    This util uses the SHA-265 algorithm to hash data.
    It implements the methods of HashUtil.
    SHA256UtilTest  
    StringEscapeUtil
    This util escapes and unescapes Strings for HTML and JSON.
    It uses the StringEscapeUtils.
    StringEscapeUtilTest  
    TeachingType
    This dataclass contains field to hold information about the teaching types
    TeachingType_  
    TeachingTypeDao
    Data Access Object providing methods to get TeachingTypes out of the Database
    Trainee
    Class that holds all the informations of an trainee.
    Trainee_  
    TraineeDao
    Data Access Object providing methods to get Trainees out of the Database
    TraineeRemoveServlet
    This servlet can be used to remove a Trainees Godfather (POST) or to delete the Trainees account itself (DELETE).
    Allowed http methods: POST, DELETE
    URIParameterEncryptionUtil
    This util encrypts URI parameters to prevent the user from guessing the values.
    URIParamterEncryptionUtilTest  
    Usermode
    This enum contains the three user-types to easily determine which user is logged in.
